05.It is assumed that there will be no major changes to the Lighting design and arc / str model which will greatly affect the coordination works. hence, additional hours may incur to accommodate the said changes

07.The document DFW TERMINAL F-PHASE 1 - WS Submittal REV 1 do not include Level 4 drawings for this scope during the MHE preparation,  it is assumed that the light layout on rooms is similar with Level 4 in SOW-03 with minimal differences. The proposed hours is subject to change once latest information is received

Name: Fab Factory Tools
Detail:
• Wall subdivider - Tool which cuts a wall into standard cuts with the following functionalities:
  ○ Create interface where it will list all parameters that the users need to input: (offset, balance, standard cut)
  ○ this will create IDs for each wall cut this way
  ○ Interface will also show in a window the output before it is applied
  ○ 2 approaches can be done here:
   § 1st is by doing it in Parts & Divide parts
   § 2nd way will be via cutting wall elements
   § (will need to get advise with team what is the best workflow for them)
 • If there is still time for the development of the tool, we can proceed with the 
  ○ Stud framework Creator tool
   § This tool will allow the auto placement of stud framework on the selected wall based on a set parameters
   § It is not estimated to do all the intended auto calculation and stuff but the tool will produce a Minimum Value Product (MVP)
  ○ Fabrication sheet creator tool
   § This tool will produce a fabrication sheet from the selected wall with all of its related components: Sheathing, studs, insulation etc.
Fabrication sheet will include a schedule and a front & top view of the wall complete with dimensions and tags.
